----
Steps
----

Environment
1. Set up Jekyll environment (incl. ruby)


Basic
1. Set up your github page (has to be public in the start)
2. Set Custom domain in github
3. Set namecheap server to github pages: https://www.namecheap.com/support/knowledgebase/article.aspx/9645/2208/how-do-i-link-my-domain-to-github-pages
4. Point nameservers to cloudflare (and set up in cloudflare) :  https://www.namecheap.com/support/knowledgebase/article.aspx/9607/2210/how-to-set-up-dns-records-for-your-domain-in-cloudflare-account
5. Make pagerule in cloudflare to enforce https: see middle of: https://blog.cloudflare.com/secure-and-fast-github-pages-with-cloudflare/
5. Set repo private (1) and wait for dns modification (up to 24h)
6. For CMS: (Set up cloudcannon: https://cloudcannon.com/)


Website
1. Pick a theme: http://jekyllthemes.org/
2. 

SEO
1. Set up Google Analyitics and Google Optimize
2.

